mediaNotes: Recorded at 5:05. Different bird from the earlier cuts. This bird is singing with "chebunk," the usual form used for dawn singing. Pieplow calls this "tsi-burrt." It is very similar to Least Flycatcher's "chebec."

Started calling and agitated a nearby Alder Flycatcher which you can hear throughout this recording giving its " peet " call with a few agitated notes added in the beginning. The Alder eventually chased it across the path and left. I used this call to bring it in and stimulate its other call, ML161791991.
